                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.154/43: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-09T17:00:00-05:45"
                            >July 9, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>183. My 176, June 28, 4 p.m. General Williams has a telegram from the Navy
                    Department inquiring concerning the length of time the engineers will be needed
                    and the magnitude of the work they will supervise. I have just seen President
                    Moncada and he said the engineers will be needed for at least six months and
                    that he proposes to spend at least $25,000 monthly on road construction in the
                    bandit area. He said that he would also greatly appreciate the assistance of the
                    engineers in conjunction with other public works now under construction or
                    projected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
